        "name": "QoI relevance to clinical failure mode — Level 3",
        "description": "The primary QoI (peak bone-cement interface tensile stress) must be directly linked to the clinically relevant failure mode (aseptic loosening) through a documented failure criterion (e.g., cement fatigue limit from ISO 5833 or published literature). Secondary QoI (cement mantle von Mises stress distribution) must be documented as supporting evidence."
      },
      "rationale": "Peak bone-cement interface tensile stress is the primary QoI, linked to aseptic loosening via cement fatigue limit of 4.5 MPa (ISO 5833 Annex C; Krause et al. 2018 JBJS). Predicted peak stress of 3.1 MPa (worst-case geometry variant) is below the fatigue limit with a safety factor of 1.45. Secondary QoI (von Mises stress distribution) confirms localized stress concentration at tray periphery consistent with clinical retrieval findings. Level 3 achieved."
