        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Constitutive model justification for cement and bone — Level 3",
        "description": "Selection of constitutive models for bone cement (linear elastic with creep), cortical bone (transversely isotropic elastic), and trabecular bone (CT-derived isotropic elastic) must be justified by published literature and sensitivity analysis. Alternative model forms (e.g., viscoelastic cement, anisotropic trabecular bone) must be considered and their exclusion documented."
      },
      "rationale": "Linear elastic cement model with power-law creep (Verdonschot & Huiskes 1997) selected based on loading rate (quasi-static gait) and cement age (fully cured, post-operative). Sensitivity analysis (VR-03) showed creep contribution <3% to peak stress at gait loading rates. Anisotropic trabecular bone model was considered; Sobol sensitivity index for trabecular anisotropy ratio was 0.04, supporting isotropic simplification. Model form justification documented in Design Verification Report DVR-TKA-2024-001. Level 3 achieved."
