        "description": "Uncertainty in key model inputs (cement elastic modulus, bone modulus, tibial tray geometry) must be characterized with probability distributions derived from published literature or direct measurement. Monte Carlo propagation must quantify the contribution of each input to QoI uncertainty. Dominant inputs must be identified and their source data documented."
      },
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo analysis (n=1000) propagated uncertainty in cement modulus (1.5–3.5 GPa, log-normal, Lewis & Younger 2004), bone modulus (CT-derived ±15%, Rho et al. 1995), and tibial tray geometry (manufacturing tolerance ±0.15 mm, drawing NGL-TKA-2024-DWG-007). Dominant input: cement modulus (Sobol first-order index 0.61). 90th-percentile peak stress: 3.8 MPa (below 4.5 MPa fatigue limit). All input sources documented in DVR-TKA-2024-001 Appendix B. Level 3 achieved."
